==English==

===Etymology===
* First attested in 1614.
* From {{etyl|la}} {{term|acclivitas|acclīvitās|lang=la}}, from {{term|acclivis|acclīvis|ascending|lang=la}}, from {{term|ad|lang=la}} + {{term|clivus|clīvus|slope|lang=la}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ə.ˈklɪv.ə.ti/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|acclivit|ies}}

# A slope or inclination of the earth, as the side of a hill, considered as ''ascending'', in opposition to ''[[declivity]]'', or ''descending''; an upward slope; [[ascent]].

